Sentencas: The lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF)-Ag composite cathode material was prepared in aqueous solution by new one-step method.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: In this method silver nanoparticles obtained by the reduction of [Ag(NH3)(2)](+) complex with sucrose were directly deposited onto the surface of LSCF powder.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: UV-Vis spectra of supernatant solution taken during synthesis showed the presence of a sharp excitation band near 397 nm attributed to the surface plasmon excitation of silver nanoparticles.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: Obtained composite powder was sintered to samaria doped ceria electrolyte in one step sintering procedure at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: The presence of silver in LSCF cathode facilitates the oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: The comparison of impedance spectra of LSCF-Ag cathodes with spectra reported in literature for similar LSCF cathodes shows that this effect is important at lower oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure

Sentencas: The analysis of the electrochemical impedance spectra recorded in the range 10(-2)-10(10) Hz reveals that the second high frequency semicircle ascribed to the electrolyte grain boundary impedance is distorted due to process belonging to oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Composite cathode material LSCF-Ag for solid oxide fuel cells obtained in one step sintering procedure
